; Regression test for issue #524: --lots do not subtract when price
; precision is small (https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/524).
;
; When a lot price computed from @@ (total cost) has a non-terminating
; decimal expansion (e.g. 23.60 / 23 = 1.02608695652...), ledger rounds
; it to amount.precision + commodity.precision + 6 digits internally.
; A user referencing that lot via its displayed value (e.g. {1.026087 EUR})
; stores a strictly different rational.  Previously the two annotated
; commodities failed to combine, leaving the Broker account with both
; +23 APPL and -15 APPL lots instead of a net +8 APPL lot.
;
; The fuzzy-match path in commodity_pool_t::find_or_create now merges
; such references with the originating computed lot when their prices
; agree to the lesser of the two precisions.

commodity APPL
    note Apple
    format 1,000.00 APPL

commodity EUR
    note Euro
    format 1,000.00 EUR

2017-01-20 Buy Apple
    Broker:Stock                       23 APPL @@ 23.60 EUR
    Openning:Balance

2017-11-28 Sell Apple
    Broker:Stock                        -15 APPL {1.026087 EUR} [2017-01-20] @@ 24.00 EUR
    Broker:Profits

test bal broker --lots
8.00 APPL {1.02608696 EUR} [2017/01/20]
                              15.39 EUR  Broker
           15.39 EUR    Profits
8.00 APPL {1.02608696 EUR} [2017/01/20]    Stock
--------------------
8.00 APPL {1.02608696 EUR} [2017/01/20]
                              15.39 EUR
end test

; The same journal, reported as a plain balance, should net out to a
; single non-zero APPL holding (not two offsetting rows).
test bal broker
           8.00 APPL
           15.39 EUR  Broker
           15.39 EUR    Profits
           8.00 APPL    Stock
--------------------
           8.00 APPL
           15.39 EUR
end test
